1336
02:42:34,000 --> 02:42:40,500
So this is a natural good use for much of that ARPA funding.

1337
02:42:40,500 --> 02:43:02,000
So money from ARPA can be utilized to help with viral infection mitigation infrastructure with these renovations and new builds and the state has an interest in keeping these facilities updated and continuing to provide care for the most vulnerable in our society.

1338
02:43:02,000 --> 02:43:09,500
These places are important assets to our state and should be a source of pride.

1339
02:43:09,500 --> 02:43:19,500
The bill I present to you today was modeled after the school building aid program already in place in statute.

1340
02:43:19,500 --> 02:43:30,500
Establishing a County Nursing Home Capital Reserve Fund administered by DHHS is appropriate since DHHS works alongside these County Nursing Home projects.

1341
02:43:30,500 --> 02:43:38,500
They approve plans and make sure the requirements are met and licenses can be kept intact.

1342
02:43:38,500 --> 02:43:48,500
They therefore understand the need, the plans, and the cost of any county nursing home renovation or new build project.

1343
02:43:48,500 --> 02:44:04,500
They can also help determine how much money the project would be eligible for from a fund, such as this, based on the number of beds and who those beds will serve.

1344
02:44:04,500 --> 02:44:10,500
It will be an easy fit for DHHS to administer this fund.

1345
02:44:10,500 --> 02:44:25,500
I'm proposing that the state seeds this fund with $25 million by June 30, 2022 and then continue to fund it with an appropriation of $15 million every year after.

1346
02:44:25,500 --> 02:44:30,500
There's a $30 million cap that I've put on this.

1347
02:44:30,500 --> 02:44:51,500
